channel.title: I have a question about Java (RuneScape)
channel.description:
Okay, I am serious, whenever I try to run RuneScape it tells me I have to install Java for Google Chrome. I click the link it gave me, downloaded whatever it wanted me to download, and whenever I get to the part to install Java it tells me I already have it installed. I can't remove it either because it's not in the add/remove programs list. But it's not installed obviously, or else it wouldn't tell me I need it.
p.s I can't run RSBot or play with SwiftKit either
Can anyone help me?

item.dc:creator: @Lin Lin
item.description:
@Lin wrote:

Is it every Java application you try? I’d assume yes. The only suggestions I can give you is restore your system to some point ago when it worked.

Your registry might also be corrupted. You’d have to remove it manually from the installed programs list. For more information, check this link: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/429738/detecting-installed-programs-via-registry
